text:
In this Saturday, Jan. 28, 2017 file photo, President Donald Trump speaks on the telephone with Australian Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull in the Oval Office of the White House in Washington. (AP Photo/Alex Brandon, File) Trump's 2005 tax return leaked 
President Donald Trump paid a 25% tax rate in 2005, according to pages of a leaked tax return reported on MSNBC's Rachel Maddow Show on Tuesday evening . The return showed Trump earned more than $150 million in 2005 and paid $36.5 million in taxes after writing off $103 million in losses. 
Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist David Cay Johnston appeared on the show and said that someone had mailed him the pages of Trump's tax return. A statement from the White House before Maddow's show appeared to validate the authenticity of the documents. 
The White House also said that publishing Trump's return would be illegal -- a charge Maddow said was not true. This Day in Trump, Day 54: Salvaging the GOP health care bill Baby dies after its sitter has trouble reaching 911 
A 6-month-old died Saturday night after a babysitter was reportedly on hold for more than 30 minutes trying to reach 911 because of an issue that has been creating bottlenecks at Dallas' call center for months. 
That night 442 callers were put on hold for an average of 38 minutes, WFAA-TV (Channel 8) reported. 
Bridget Alex, the mother of 6-month-old Brandon, is seeking answers from the city. 
(Jack Plunkett/Invision) Photo of the morning 
Actress Melissa McCarthy drives a RYDE electric car around the ZACH Theatre parking lot before the world premiere of "Nobodies" during the South by Southwest Film Festival on Monday, in Austin. 
SXSW has made headlines recently after several international attendees have been denied entry into the U.S. 
Eloq, a Danish electronic dance music artist scheduled to perform at SXSW, said in a tweet that he was denied entry to the U.S. on Monday and detained in a small, bright room and a "very unpleasant jail cell" for 23 hours. Dallas Cowboys quarterback Ezekiel Elliott. (Tom Fox/Staff Photographer) Sports highlights
